{{Spanish name|Benoit|Vanderhorst}}
'''Pedro Bartolomé Benoit Vanderhorst ''' (February 13, 1921, [[Samaná (town)|Samaná]] – April 5, 2012) was a politician and military officer from the [[Dominican Republic]]. He served as the 7th provisional [[president of the Dominican Republic]] from 1 May until 7 May 1965. He was also a member of the Revolutionary Committee, which ruled the country for about few hours on 25 April 1965. 

